  "text": "In oxygen involving metabolisms like photorespiration and photosynthesis, reactive oxygen species (ROS) are natural byproducts [CITATION_1] Häder 2002, Apel and [CITATION_2] in phototrophic microorganisms. Typical ROS are e.g. superoxide, hydroxyl, peroxyl, and alkoxy radicals. Under nonstressed conditions, production and scavenging of ROS in these microorganisms is in equilibrium [CITATION_3] .",
